## Example 2 ‚Äî Joint Variation

Suppose `y` varies jointly as `x` and `z`. Find `y` when `x = 4` and `z = -3`, if `y = -15` when `x = -6` and `z = 1`.

Use:

`y1/(x1z1) = y2/(x2z2)`

`y/(4(-3)) = -15/(-6(1))`

`y/(-12) = -15/(-6)`

`y = -30`

